description: From Latin inexsuperabilis, from in- (“not”) + exsuperabilis (“that may be surmounted”). See in- (“not”) +‎ ex- +‎ superable.

adjectives.description: inexsuperable (comparative more inexsuperable, superlative most inexsuperable)

entries.meaning: (archaic) Not capable of being passed over; insuperable; insurmountable.
